Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Salad Potatoes{350%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @Olive Oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @Ciabatta{1} and evenly spread over the garlic.

Cut the ciabatta into 2cm chunks.

Pop the ciabatta croutons onto a #baking tray{} in a single layer.

Drizzle with @Olive Oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat well.

Bake the croutons and @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90%grams} on the middle shelf until golden and crispy, ~{8-10%minutes}, then remove from the oven and set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook it thoroughly.

Meanwhile, halve the @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125%grams}.

Drain and tear the @Mozzarella{1%ball} into 2cm chunks.

Cut the @Lemon{1} into wedges.

== Pesto Dressing ==

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @Pesto{32%grams}, @Mayonnaise{32%grams}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Olive Oil{1/2%tbsp} for the dressing (see pantry for both amounts) along with a good squeeze of lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper and mix to combine.

Once combined, toss the tomatoes through the dressing.

== Assembly ==

When everything's ready, add the roasted potatoes, @Baby Leaf Mix{50%grams}, bacon and croutons to the #salad bowl{} and toss until evenly coated in the dressing.

Share the salad between your #serving bowls{}. Top with the mozzarella chunks.

Finish by drizzling over the @Balsamic Glaze{12%milliliter} and sprinkling with the @Hazelnuts{25%grams}.

Enjoy!